This paper discusses the censorship policies of Chinese search engines, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The study also involves analyzing the filtering of specific keywords, which could be categorized under cybercrime (cs.CY) and social media (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques to conduct the experiments, which could be relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
